The division between Keijō and Ranan Gokoku Shrines was based on domicile, residence, and unit affiliation:
* [[:en:Gangwon|Gangwon Province (Japanese rule)]], [[:en:South Hamgyong Province|South Hamgyong Province (Japanese rule)]], and [[:en:North Hamgyong Province|North Hamgyong Province (Japanese rule)]] were assigned to {{ill|Ranan Gokoku Shrine|ja|羅南護国神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ranan Gokoku Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
* [[:en:Gyeonggi Province|Gyeonggi Province (Japanese rule)]], [[:en:North Chungcheong Province|North Chungcheong Province (Japanese rule)]], [[:en:South Chungcheong Province|South Chungcheong Province (Japanese rule)]], {{ill|North Jeolla Province (Japanese rule)|ja|全羅北道|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/North Jeolla Province (Japanese rule)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 全北特別自治道}}, [[:en:South Jeolla Province|South Jeolla Province (Japanese rule)]], [[:en:North Pyongan Province|North Pyongan Province (Japanese rule)]], and [[:en:South Pyongan Province|South Pyongan Province (Japanese rule)]] were assigned to Keijō Gokoku Shrine.

